Running a Windows 98 VM in Virtualbox
Download Microsoft Windows 98 Download
Extract the Windows 98 files
Launch Virtualbox
Create a New VM by selecting Machine > New
Name: Windows 98
Machine Folder: C:\VMs
Type: Microsoft Windows
Version: Windows 98
Memory Size: 512 MB
Hard disk: Create a virtual hard disk now

Click Create
On the Create Virtual Hard Disk dialog
Name the virtual disk image Windows 98.vdi
File size: 1.00 GB
Hard disk file type: VDI
Storage on physical hard disk: Dynamically Allocated

Click Create
Select the VM and Click Settings
Select Storage
Click on the CD-ROM drive
Select the disc dropdown to the right > Choose a virtual optical disc file...
Browse to the extracted Windows 98 files and select Win98 .iso
Click OK
Make sure the Windows 98 VM is selected and click Start > Normal
Press 2 to Boot from CD-ROM
Press 1 to Start Windows 98 Setup from CD-ROM
Press Enter to Continue with Setup 
Press Enter to Configure unallocated disk space
Select Yes to enable large disk support, press Enter
Press Enter to continue
Press 2 to Boot from CD-ROM
Press 1 to Start Windows 98 Setup from CD-ROM
Press Enter to Continue with Setup
Click the Continue button to begin installing Windows
Follow the prompts to give the machine a name and workgroup
Wait for the files to copy and Windows 98 to complete initializing
When the VM reboots, select 1 to Boot from the Hard Disk
Enter a name and company on the User Information Dialog, click Next
Select I accept the Agreement, click Next
Enter a valid Windows 98 SE product key (H8J3X-9HQQG-DQXX7-6GFTJ-DF6MB), click Next
Click Finish
Set the date/time and select a timezone > Click Apply > Click OK
Wait for Windows to Update Sytstem Settings
At the login screen click OK
Enjoy the boot up sound from the Gods
Welcome back to Windows 98
Revel in the nostalgia
